President Biden addressed the recent acts of terror in Texas and a synagogue during a press conference. He commended the local authorities and FBI for their cooperation and efforts in handling the incidents. The President emphasized that these acts of violence, particularly antisemitism, will not be tolerated, and he plans to reach out to synagogues and places of worship to ensure their safety. When asked about the gunman's acquisition of weapons, Biden stated that the assertion is that he purchased them on the street upon arriving in the country. The President also highlighted the importance of background checks and addressing gun sales to prevent such incidents. Biden mentioned that more details will be provided during a press conference on Wednesday. He acknowledged that there is still limited information about the motivations behind targeting the synagogue and the individual's demands for the release of a prisoner.